    {
      "num": 11,
      "text": "A CFE is analyzing the accounts payable records of a manufacturing company with 8,400 vendor transactions over the past year. After applying Benford's Law to the first digit of invoice amounts, the CFE observes that invoices beginning with the digit '9' appear 14.2% of the time, significantly exceeding the expected frequency of 4.6%. The company uses a decentralized purchasing system where department managers can approve invoices up to $9,999 without senior oversight. Which analytical procedure should the CFE perform next to assess the fraud risk indicated by this deviation?",
