      "num": 12,
      "text": "A CFE is analyzing a company's general ledger and notices that the suspense account contains numerous journal entries posted by the CFO during the final week of each quarter. A Benford's Law analysis of the first digits of these suspense account entries shows a significantly lower frequency of entries beginning with 1 (12%) compared to the expected frequency (30.1%), while entries beginning with 9 appear at 18% versus the expected 4.6%. What should the CFE conclude from this digital analysis?",
