    },
    {
      "num": 13,
      "text": "A forensic accountant is analyzing journal entries posted to a suspense account at a manufacturing company over a 12-month period. The dataset contains 2,847 entries with dollar amounts ranging from $125 to $847,500. A Benford's Law analysis reveals that the digit '5' appears as the first digit in 24% of the entries, while the digit '1' appears in only 18% of entries. The expected Benford frequency for '1' is approximately 30% and for '5' is approximately 8%. Which analytical conclusion is most appropriate based on these findings?",
      "tag": "Forensic Analysis - Benford's Law and Suspense Account Manipulation",
