      "question": "A certified fraud examiner is investigating potential sales fraud at a manufacturing company. The CFE has obtained 24 months of data and wants to use regression analysis to identify unusual patterns. The data includes monthly sales revenue, number of sales transactions, advertising expenditure, and seasonal factors.\n\nWhich of the following statements regarding the use of regression analysis in this fraud examination is MOST accurate?",
      "options": [
        "The CFE should use sales revenue as the independent variable to predict the number of transactions, as revenue drives transaction volume",
